	<td bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	<td class="subjectbar" height="20" style="font-size: 8pt;padding-left:10px;" width="100%">
		Re: Priest Balance - Clerics

	</td>
	
		<td class="subjectbar" align=right style="padding:0px;padding-right:10px;">












		<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 id="io_bclericbalancem318_table" 
		
			onClick="setId('318');showLiMenu(this,'io_bclericbalancem318','right',false);" 
			onDblClick="setId('318');showLiMenu(this,'io_bclericbalancem318','right',false);" 
			
		>
		<tr class=clickable>
			
				<td nowrap><a class=subjectbar_text style='font-size: 8pt;'>Options</a></td>
				
			<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
			<td><img src='/i/skins/default/button_options.gif' border=0 alt='Options' title='Options' width=11 height=28></td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
		</table>
		
		</td></tr>
		
	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=3539'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#CC6600;font-weight:bold; '>Andinadinadina</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Master<br>
			
				Posts: 228<br>
				
				Registered: 03-05-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=3539'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&message.id=318#M318">4</a> of 11
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 306 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Vykadin wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So what needs to be balanced? Do druids and shamans need more healing? Maybe. I don't really know, nor do I care. Do I mind if they can fill in for a cleric's role better in end game encounters? Not at all. I see druids spot healing in my guild's raids all the time. I have yet to see a druid sit in for a cleric in a CH rotation however. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>The CH rotations are one of the few things I might not mind giving up, or at least giving ground on.&nbsp; One suggestion I remember reading on the cleric boards was give clerics a spell that allows druids to cast a cleric equivalent CH for a&nbsp;while.&nbsp; This keeps&nbsp;clerics required in raids&nbsp;but lets a raid happen with less clerics overall, which in my opinion is a good thing.&nbsp; I don't think druids liked the idea very much, and in a way I can see why.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr **SMURF**"MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>Am I against raising the druids and shaman's healing powers? Not at all, but that would come with a caveat. I may be called selfish, but what do I get out of raising druid/shaman healing? My class lacks utility. Generally. I can't invis. I can't levitate. I can't solo efficiently. Period. I can't quad, or charm for awsome experience. Nor is the cleric class alone in this. Many other classes have no soloing options. Warriors, Rogues and Paladins are stuck with the grouping dilemma as well. So am I asking to be given the ability to solo? Well, it would be nice, but how to do it without stepping on other classes toes or making me some sort of amazing holy warrior? Frankly I don't have any answers to this.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>Personally, while I'd like an option to solo and get reasonable xp for it, I don't want to do it at the expense of my group desireability.&nbsp; I played a wizard for quite a while before I made&nbsp;my cleric, and a big part of the reason I wanted a cleric was because I was tired of sitting on small desert islands by myself and killing dinosaurs.&nbsp; That group desireability was one of the main selling points of the cleric class for me, and if it's going to be diminished there had better be a good reason for it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I do take issue with the idea that druids and shaman need significantly&nbsp;better heals in the first place though.&nbsp; There are many druids out there who want nothing more than a little tweaking here and there, and&nbsp;that's fine by me, a slightly improved blast heal for druids isn't going to hurt me&nbsp;that much I don't think.&nbsp; But there are some who want to raise their healing abilities to the point where they can main heal *any* group (I'm not sure if these people are a very loud fringe or the majority, sometimes it's hard to tell).&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;This does not make sense to me.&nbsp; Clerics are, and always have been, the top healing class in the game.&nbsp; What would the point be of having the best heals, if in any situation, the second best heals are good enough?&nbsp; Unlike dps, healing doesn't stack past a point.&nbsp; You never need more healing than the dps that is being inflicted on your group.&nbsp; So having more than enough is superfluous.&nbsp; What did they think, when they created a druid, that the cleric class was there for?&nbsp; In my opinion, the ones who are complaining didn't think.&nbsp; What they thought was "I'll be able to buff and heal and nuke and debuff and DS and port and dot."&nbsp; But the thing is, you CAN'T do all of these things well enough that you replace the classes that do them to exclusion, or else there's no point in having the specialist classes at all.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr **SMURF**"MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>Clerics have a lot of great spells. We have great buffs, great heals, great rezzes. I don't mind that my best buff isn't used in the end game in favor of Symbol and the druids 9 spells. I think its great that the classes working together are more powerful then alone. I don't really even mind the peridot costs these days. I'm long past the ability to spend my platinum on gear upgrades or spells, and HoV only costs me 2 peridots. I do remember a time though when I was constantly pressed for cash and peridot costs were more then I could easily afford. I still feel for the lower level classes and this is definitely something I think should be reconsidered at low levels.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>I'm still at a point in the game where my peri costs are an annoyance.&nbsp; I don't have to scrounge or spend hours chasing hill giants around anymore, but it is still a pain in the butt.&nbsp; And it's a cost I fail to understand.&nbsp; Why does symbol require a peri, but 9 doesn't?&nbsp; If anything, out of the two I'd rather have a 9 because it stacks with focus, my own mana regen wont.&nbsp; I suppose the original idea was to use the reagent as a means to limit the spells usage, but since it's fairly obvious that didn't happen and is not going to happen, perhaps it could be reconsidered.&nbsp; I think this is something that should be looked at as an issue seperate from any other class balancing though (with the exception of the few other classes who incur costs like this every time they group) as it's just not terribly fair.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr **SMURF**"MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Cleric balance so far has consisted of upgrading our hammers, Yaulp VI, and lowering the cost of casting our little hammer pet. These were a semi decent start, however they did the vast majority of lower level clerics absolutely nothing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>If by semi decent you mean not terribly decent at all, I'd agree.&nbsp; Yaulp is the only one out of the three that really and truly helps me, and even that only gets rare usage.&nbsp; The only thing the summoned hammer really helps me do is stay awake.&nbsp; I still meet people who are under the impression that cleric melee is pretty nice, because they see all the procs in a row.&nbsp; Add up those procs sometime over the course of a minute or two.&nbsp; We can do more damage with less effort with a nuke (which Vykadin covers pretty well in his post, I just wanted to reinforce it).&nbsp; Clerics who think they're doing mad dps with their hammers are delusional.&nbsp; And yes,&nbsp;I've actually&nbsp;met clerics who think this, I suppose they're the equivalent of those warriors who think they're doing most of the damage to the mobs that come in.</DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr **SMURF**"MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>&nbsp;1. Plate Mitigation - We are the only priest class that can wear plate armor (shaman wear chain and druids leather) yet we are put on the same plate mitigation table as casters. That means that all that heavy plate we wear might as well be cloth for all the good it does us. Take an enchanter and a cleric with equal AC and we both take the same damage from a hit that lands. We are a plate class, so we should have the benefit of being a plate class. I'm not asking for my dodge skill to be raised or anything like that. I just think that as a plate wearing, mace weilding cleric I should be able to stand there and laugh at the mob a little as they pound on me and I cast my heals.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>This would be nice.&nbsp; If we have to compete with melee for our gear, we should get the same benifits from it that they do.&nbsp; The sheets of steel covering my body should be more than ornamental.</DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr **SMURF**"MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>Well, upping my plate mitigation is at least a start. I think that raising my melee and defense skills shouldn't be completely out of line either, at least to slightly below the knight classes so as not to step on their toes. And frankly, against undead I should be a killing machine. If more of my AA were tailored to killing undead I would definitely invest the points. Which brings me to my next suggestion.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>I would like this too.&nbsp; I think it'd be fun.&nbsp; But I think paladins would pitch a hissy-fit about it and we'd get any concessions nerfed into oblivion, just like before.&nbsp; I'd like to be optimistic about it, but I just can't see it actually happening.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr **SMURF**"MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>3. Fix the AA ability Turn Undead</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>I never bought Turn Undead, because I'd read how bad it is.&nbsp; Be nice to make it actually useful, but I think making it anything like Slay Undead would, again, draw the wrath of the paladins.&nbsp; And in this case, as much as I'd love to smite undead for crazy damage, I can see the paladin viewpoint.&nbsp; This is one of their pretty neat toys, and if I were them I wouldn't want it infringed upon.</DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4. Fix the AA ability Divine Avatar - this is another great idea gone bad. For the AA points this costs it should turn me into a monster for meleeing. Of course with all of our horrid melee skill caps it means that instead of hitting for like 50 max when I hit, I hit for 52 max. Great, instead of 50, miss, miss, miss, 50, miss, 50, miss, miss, miss. I hit for 52, miss, miss, miss, 52, miss, miss, 52, miss. Again, this should be a passive skill that increases our melee damage or skills. Restrict it to undead if you must, I don't care. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>I sometimes wonder about the people who put together and test the different aa skills for the classes.&nbsp; I'm pretty sure that a lot of it's just put in to waste people's time, as there is no way a reasonable person could consider some of this stuff useful.&nbsp; Divine Avatar, from everything I've heard, is total junk.&nbsp; At least I can take comfort in the knowledge that other classes have some things as useless as this in their lineup.</DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>5. Utility Spells </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>I agree on this one.&nbsp; Would be nice, not really necessary.&nbsp; I certainly don't want to get invis, lev, and eb as compensation for losing my healing edge.&nbsp; It'd be like giving defensive to pallys and sks, and giving warriors Gate.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr **SMURF**"MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>Are there other areas I think that could be used to balance the priest classes a little bit? yes. Some of them we have seen implemented. Spell casting haste, and the damage mitigation spells are interesting and I think they should scale up from lower levels where they are weaker then they are currently, to the current levels where they are stronger. I've seen lots of people talk about "curses." Do I think clerics should be given a line of "curse" spells? Well it would certainly be an area of specialization that could be unique to clerics. I wouldn't be against it, but it would really be a class changing line of spells. Cursing the mob's attack rating or strength or speed, or spell casting ability would be cool and fun, but not the reason I started a cleric.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>I would not like something like this.&nbsp; I didn't&nbsp;choose my class&nbsp;to debuff, and I'd rather leave things like this to the people that did.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr **SMURF**"MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>The trend in cleric balancing has been fleshing us out as a "battle cleric" and I think that is really the direction we should be going especially versus undead. Pound per pound a cleric or a paladin should be able to make the undead of Norrath quake in their bones. Solo should be at least a slow but effective option for us. Druids and shaman should probably be able to step up to the healer plate in the end game, even with rezzes in a pinch. Clerics probably shouldn't be the forced money sinks throughout most of the game. There are at least two completely useless cleric AA that should be completely revamped. Clerics should remain the kings and queens of healing, but I don't think that most of us would be averse to increases in the druid and shaman healing as long as we are thrown at least a few bones along the way. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>I do like the 'battle cleric' idea, but I just can't see it happening.&nbsp; I can't see them giving us a melee skill with any degree of actual usefulness without the other melee classes going nuts about it.&nbsp; And as for the druids and shaman healing end game...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I have to disagree on this point.&nbsp; I do not think that druids and shaman&nbsp; should be able to tackle the main healing job in the end game.&nbsp; The ability to do that&nbsp;is what <EM>makes</EM> the cleric class.&nbsp; It's <EM>everything</EM> we're made for.&nbsp; I understand some are advocating a complete rebalancing, but they should realize that in doing so they are going to be completely changing a class (probably moreso than any other class in the game has been changed thus far)&nbsp;and changing the underlying reason that many many clerics chose the class they did.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you are going with something that sweeping and drastic, the bones thrown to us are going to need an awful lot of meat on them, and I just don't think that will happen.&nbsp; Give us not enough, and you've effectively ruined clerics.&nbsp; Give us too much and you're stepping all over other classes.&nbsp; The balance is the key, and (I've said it before, I'll say it again...) after the last round of priest rebalancing, I don't think I'm inclined to expect them the get the balance right.&nbsp; They would have to remold the cleric class into something almost&nbsp;entirely new.&nbsp; Berserkers were the last new class in EQ, look how well they're doing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr **SMURF**"MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Most of us who play clerics as our mains are pretty nice folks. We are forced to group and are therefore pretty sociable. As a rule, we will go out of our way to rez someone in need. Cleric burn out takes its toll. More and more of us are becoming bots as we have no real soloing options for when we can't find groups. This leads to a vicious circle of there not being enough clerics at the end game, increased cleric bots, and druids and shaman wanting more healing power so that raids aren't delayed by the stranglehold that they perceive clerics as having on raid healing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>Cleric burn-out is only going to get worse if something is done&nbsp;and it's done wrong.&nbsp; I picked a cleric to excel at something.&nbsp; If the fact that I excel at what I do is made pointless, you can't compensate me by making me less than the best at a bunch of other roles that are already filled satisfactorily or you are going to waltz all over the classes that already do these things.&nbsp; And anyway, if I wanted a class that took bits and pieces from other classes, I would have played one.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It's not that I'm really adverse to change, it's that I have zero faith that the changes will be done well.&nbsp; I don't think anything would come of it but clerics losing ground in the one and only thing they really have to lose.&nbsp; To expand clerics to the extent that you and other people think would be satisfactory in order to bring other priests up to par, would require something of a consensus from more than just the priest classes.&nbsp; I can not realisticly see us getting it.</DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>Well enough of my drunken ramblings. See you all in game soon I hope.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Vyk, Level 65 Cleric</DIV>
<DIV>Drunken Dorf</DIV>
<DIV>Torvonnilous</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>I need more beer&nbsp;<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-sad.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
