			<P>Hate to burst all your bubbles, but "balance" will never happen in regards to the cleric class. The first time it was promised to us, and every other class, (all the old school player will remember this one) was on the Whineplay boards, similar to this. They stopped after druids and rangers then denied they were every going to "balance" the classes. The second time, they increased the healing power of druids and shaman and gave us a fun new summoned hammer which got nerfed within the first hour it went live. </P>
<P>The game is entrentched in the uberness of complete heal chains. Complete Heal is the single biggest flaw in this game, and the only way things will ever change is either A) Getting rid of complete heal altogether and re-tuning content to match or B) Give FULL complete heals to druids AND shaman while giving alot of utility and DPS spells/abilities to clerics. Neither of these senarios is going to happen. The last time clerics got&nbsp;a raise in DPS (summoned hammer) all it took was a post from 1 lone paladin to get it nerfed. </P>
