			<DIV>As a druid I completely agree with the cle's out there that think they should bring more to a group then healing. You should, unfortunatly design problems and "Class envy" cause way to many problems. As a cle you should be the best at healing however you should melee somewhere between where you do now and where Pals do (Closer to the Pal side) Of couse this would piss every pal in the game off. Agains undead mobs you should nuke like a wizard and dot like a necro. Atleast have some undead only AA that is comparable to the pal AA SU, why should the undead have more to fear from a Cle/War mix then a pure Cle.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As for druid and Shaman healing. I personally do not want to be a main healer, its not my choice. If I wanted to be a main healer I would play a cleric. However druids are being forced into the main healing role simply because 1/6th of the playing community is not cle's. If it were not for&nbsp;GoD I would say druids and shamans have more then enough in the way of healing to fill in for a cleric when they had. In GoD its just not possible, I may not want to be a main healer but when you ahve 5 people rdy to go for an hour but are unable to find a cle willing to come it gets annoying. Or if your fighting away and you cle decides to leave you are forced to find another cle to replace them where if any other class left you would have choices&nbsp;of what class to replace them with.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As for that comparason between druid and clerics healing and nuking both numbers are off. No a cle can not nuke 74% as well as a druid. I would say its more like 50% is not more like 40%. One the same note druids can not heal even 63% as well as clerics. A druid can CH and bast heal 63% of what a cleric can however a cleric can also HoT, Group HoT, Group Heal, Group CH (even though its not used much) and Fast heal. And no you cant really count SoWood as a HoT being as it can only be used once every 21 minutes.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If SoE would tone down GoD to the point that a druid or shaman could fill in if a cle was unavailable then I would be more then happy with the druid healing ability. I think the only reason most druids are complaining about healing is that the only healer capable of healing in GoD is cle's meaning that if you dont have a cleric you dont do it. In PoP you can exp anywhere wihtout a cle however having a cleric makes the group far more efficient and the exp much easier, GoD should be the same. a group in GoD should be capable of fighting without a cleric however having a cle should make it much easier. Like I said before I dont want to main heal for a group however I want to know that if we search for a cle for an hour and dont find 1 that I could fill in as the healer and atleast have a reasonable chance that the group will not die,</DIV>
<DIV></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>04-28-2004</span> <span class=time_text>08:59 AM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
